(
<figureCitation box="[597,700,232,256]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="9.[125,185,1610,1629]" captionTargetBox="[170,1128,903,1574]" captionTargetId="figure-161@9.[170,1128,903,1574]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figure 2. Amiota (Amiota) subsinuata Chen and Aotsuza, sp. nov. „. (A) Epandrium and cercus, lateral view; (B) surstylus and tenth sternite, ventral view; (C, D) hypandrium, gonopod, parameres and aedeagal apodeme: (C) ventral view, (D) lateral view; (E) ejaculatory apodeme. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4657900" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4657900/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="272">Figure 2</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[125,1172,200,335]" pageId="9" pageNumber="272">
<emphasis box="[125,238,279,303]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="272">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Vertical lobe of gonopod extremely elongated basally, forming one pair of strongly curved, rod-shaped processes with one sickle-like projection submedially (
<figureCitation box="[975,1137,311,335]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="9.[125,185,1610,1629]" captionTargetBox="[170,1128,903,1574]" captionTargetId="figure-161@9.[170,1128,903,1574]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figure 2. Amiota (Amiota) subsinuata Chen and Aotsuza, sp. nov. „. (A) Epandrium and cercus, lateral view; (B) surstylus and tenth sternite, ventral view; (C, D) hypandrium, gonopod, parameres and aedeagal apodeme: (C) ventral view, (D) lateral view; (E) ejaculatory apodeme. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4657900" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4657900/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="272">Figure 2C, D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[125,245,391,415]" box="[125,245,391,415]" pageId="9" pageNumber="272">
<emphasis box="[125,245,391,415]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="272">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[125,1173,439,527]" pageId="9" pageNumber="272">
<emphasis box="[125,214,439,463]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="272">Thorax.</emphasis>
Thorax dark yellow, medially with one broadened, brown stripe, and laterally with two thin versicolour stripes; pleura yellow, with brown patch on upper half; scutellum dark yellow, with brown margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[125,1172,566,625]" pageId="9" pageNumber="272">
<emphasis box="[125,193,566,590]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="272">Wing.</emphasis>
Ventral surface of costal vein with 
<emphasis box="[605,629,567,590]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="272">ca</emphasis>
14–15 distinct, peg-like spinules between R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1139,1172,576,593]" fontSize="7" pageId="9" pageNumber="272">2+3</subScript>
and R 
<subScript attach="right" box="[197,230,607,625]" fontSize="7" pageId="9" pageNumber="272">4+5</subScript>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[125,1172,662,718]" pageId="9" pageNumber="272">
<emphasis box="[125,341,662,686]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="272">Abdominal tergites.</emphasis>
Abdominal tergites dark brown; second yellow medially; third and fourth with yellow stripe medially; fifth and sixth entirely black.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[125,1173,758,845]" lastBlockId="10.[138,1186,137,225]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="273" pageId="9" pageNumber="272">
<emphasis box="[125,305,758,782]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="272">Male terminalia.</emphasis>
Epandrium with 
<emphasis box="[508,532,758,781]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="272">ca</emphasis>
10–11 setae near posterior margin and at postero-ventral corner (
<figureCitation box="[216,341,790,814]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="9.[125,185,1610,1629]" captionTargetBox="[170,1128,903,1574]" captionTargetId="figure-161@9.[170,1128,903,1574]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figure 2. Amiota (Amiota) subsinuata Chen and Aotsuza, sp. nov. „. (A) Epandrium and cercus, lateral view; (B) surstylus and tenth sternite, ventral view; (C, D) hypandrium, gonopod, parameres and aedeagal apodeme: (C) ventral view, (D) lateral view; (E) ejaculatory apodeme. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4657900" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4657900/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="272">Figure 2A</figureCitation>
). Surstylus with 
<emphasis box="[536,560,790,813]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="272">ca</emphasis>
seven prensisetae (
<figureCitation box="[783,907,790,814]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="9.[125,185,1610,1629]" captionTargetBox="[170,1128,903,1574]" captionTargetId="figure-161@9.[170,1128,903,1574]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figure 2. Amiota (Amiota) subsinuata Chen and Aotsuza, sp. nov. „. (A) Epandrium and cercus, lateral view; (B) surstylus and tenth sternite, ventral view; (C, D) hypandrium, gonopod, parameres and aedeagal apodeme: (C) ventral view, (D) lateral view; (E) ejaculatory apodeme. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4657900" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4657900/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="272">Figure 2B</figureCitation>
). Hypandrial apodeme with two pairs of sharply pointed projections subbasally and distally. Paramere basally curved triangularly in lateral view, with a row of 
<emphasis box="[627,651,137,160]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="273">ca</emphasis>
eight or nine sensilla submedially to apically. Aedeagal apodeme very small, less sclerotized (
<figureCitation box="[691,857,169,193]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="9.[125,185,1610,1629]" captionTargetBox="[170,1128,903,1574]" captionTargetId="figure-161@9.[170,1128,903,1574]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figure 2. Amiota (Amiota) subsinuata Chen and Aotsuza, sp. nov. „. (A) Epandrium and cercus, lateral view; (B) surstylus and tenth sternite, ventral view; (C, D) hypandrium, gonopod, parameres and aedeagal apodeme: (C) ventral view, (D) lateral view; (E) ejaculatory apodeme. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4657900" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4657900/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="273">Figure 2C, D</figureCitation>
). Ejaculatory apodeme with 
<emphasis box="[138,162,201,224]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="273">ca</emphasis>
six pits on each lateral margin; stalk slightly longer than the apical plate (
<figureCitation box="[1008,1130,201,225]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="9.[125,185,1610,1629]" captionTargetBox="[170,1128,903,1574]" captionTargetId="figure-161@9.[170,1128,903,1574]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figure 2. Amiota (Amiota) subsinuata Chen and Aotsuza, sp. nov. „. (A) Epandrium and cercus, lateral view; (B) surstylus and tenth sternite, ventral view; (C, D) hypandrium, gonopod, parameres and aedeagal apodeme: (C) ventral view, (D) lateral view; (E) ejaculatory apodeme. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4657900" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4657900/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="273">Figure 2E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
